<subSubSection id="C3036541FFD88B065E8FF9372613FEDC" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD88B015E8FF937224EF917" blockId="43.[189,303,1701,1727]" box="[189,303,1701,1727]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFD88B015E8FF937224EF917" bold="true" box="[189,303,1701,1727]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015E8FF937224EF917" bold="true" box="[189,303,1701,1727]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD88B015E8FF9412637F868" blockId="43.[189,1399,1747,1985]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015E8FF94122B8F945" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[189,473,1747,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incognitus" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015E8FF94122B8F945" box="[189,473,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Ebenacobius incognitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD88B015FD1F94621A3F946" box="[483,706,1747,1774]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015A29F94127FAF945" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" box="[1051,1179,1747,1773]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015A29F94127FAF945" box="[1051,1179,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Derelomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single male deposited at SAMC (
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B3BFFD88B015FC4F96521E4F8B9" author="Hesse J. C." box="[502,645,1783,1809]" firstAuthor="Hesse" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="475 - 536" part="25" refId="ref30885" refString="Hesse J. C. 1929. Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa. Annals of the South African Museum 25: 475 - 536." title="Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa" type="journal article" year="1929">
<collectingRegion id="49DDF828FFD88B015FC4F965215FF8B9" box="[502,574,1783,1809]" country="Germany" name="Hessen" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Hesse</collectingRegion>
1929
</bibRefCitation>
). This specimen was loaned to Guillermo Kuschel (loan 24018) who undertook a study on palaeotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015C95F888204CF89C" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[679,813,1818,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
from 2007. Unfortunately he passed away before he could complete this work and left the very preliminary manuscript and the material borrowed from institutions (see postscript in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B3BFFD88B015C25F8F32186F8D2" author="Haran J. &amp; Beaudoin-Ollivier L. &amp; Benoit L. &amp; Kuschel G." box="[535,743,1888,1915]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Haran" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 32" part="684" refId="ref30703" refString="Haran J., Beaudoin-Ollivier L., Benoit L. &amp; Kuschel G. 2020. Revision of the palm-pollinating weevil genus Elaeidobius Kuschel, 1952 (Curculionidae, Curculioninae, Derelomini) with descriptions of two new species. European Journal of Taxonomy 684: 1 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2020.684" title="Revision of the palm-pollinating weevil genus Elaeidobius Kuschel, 1952 (Curculionidae, Curculioninae, Derelomini) with descriptions of two new species" type="journal article" year="2020">
Haran 
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD88B015C57F8F321C1F8D2" box="[613,672,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Despite intensive search in the material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD88B015AC3F8F22616F8D2" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[1265,1399,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
loaned, the 
<typeStatus id="54A28868FFD88B015F74F81122CCF835" box="[326,429,1923,1949]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species could not be identified and is provisionally considered as lost. This species is very distinct and specimens examined were easily identified based on Hesse’s description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFDF8B065E8FFE9A222EFE8A" blockId="44.[189,335,264,290]" box="[189,335,264,290]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFDF8B065E8FFE9A222EFE8A" bold="true" box="[189,335,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDF8B065E8FFE9A222EFE8A" bold="true" box="[189,335,264,290]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Life history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFDF8B065E8FFEAA2613FEDC" blockId="44.[189,1399,311,373]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Host plant unknown. The record on 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDF8B065C4BFEA5273CFEF9" authority="(Jacq.) Lehm." authorityName="Lehm." baseAuthorityName="Jacq." box="[633,1117,311,337]" class="Cycadopsida" family="Zamiaceae" genus="Encephalartos" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cycadales" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longifolius">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDF8B065C4BFEA520CCFEF9" box="[633,941,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Encephalartos longifolius</emphasis>
(Jacq.) Lehm.
</taxonomicName>
is accidental given the known biology of the genus. Adults were collected in March, April, August, November and December.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
